<div id='gazette_story'>
    <div align='center'>
        <font size='4'><b>READY TO GROW SOME PIZZA?</b></font><br>
                                <img src='http://graphics.millsberry.com/site_gfx/interiors/gazette/gazette_20090924.jpg' border='1' width='280' height='200'>
                        </div>
        <div id='gazette_byline'><em>By Audrey Smythe-Wei<br>Editor-in-Chief</em></div>
        <b>Thursday, September 24, 2009</b> &mdash;
    For the past few days, the citizens of Millsberry have been walking around town in overalls and bandanas. <br><br>Will Wexley, dressed in a plaid shirt and straw hat, shed light on the situation, noting, &quot;Everyone is just so eager to start farming at  <a href="http://millsberry.com/pizza_farm/">Grow Good Farms!</a> We&#039;ll be learning how to maintain crops, watch them grow, and harvest them &mdash; and we&#039;ll be <a href="http://millsberry.com/pizza_farm/">helping others</a> in the process. If you make a plain pizza, General Mills will donate $0.15 to Feeding America, an organization that delivers groceries to food banks across America... with the help of people just like you! <br><br>&quot;Each topping you add to your pizza will increase the donation by $.05 &mdash; so a banana pizza will mean $.20, a banana-basil pizza will mean $.25, etc. The more crops you grow, the more pizzas you can make &mdash; and the more money will get donated. General Mills will donate up to $6,250 each month!&quot;<br><br>That&#039;s right. From now until May 31st, 2010, Grow Good Farms is officially open to help others, and there&#039;s a <a href="http://millsberry.com/pizza_farm/">plot</a> of land waiting just for you! <br>
<br>
Farm founder Giovanna Antonia de Luca has been working hard to make sure there are tons of seeds to sow (plant), and plenty of plots ready for Millsberry&#039;s newest farmers!<br><br>Giovanna also agreed to take a break from her fieldwork to talk to The <i>Gazette</i>, to offer readers a run-down on how this fantastic enterprise began.<br><br>She explained, &quot;It started as a dream when I was still living in Italy &mdash; and wanting to do something to bring together my two passions: growing food, and helping others. Now, with Grow Good Farms, that dream has become a reality! The more farmers we have making pizzas full of tasty toppings, the more money General Mills will donate to Feeding America, up to $6,250 each month. Those pizzas will really add up fast!&quot;<br><br>Sounds like the perfect plan: Have fun farming, and help those in need! That&#039;s definitely motivation to <a href="http://millsberry.com/pizza_farm/">start your farm today!</a> And with fun and easy, step-by-step instructions, you&#039;ll be a farming-pro in no time.<br><br>In fact, with this news in hand, we lined up to start our farm &mdash; and to begin the pizza-making process &mdash; right away! We urge you to do the same!<br>
    </div>

